{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each running VM writes a PID file at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"~\/.spooktacular\/vms\/<name>.vm\/pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". The file contains the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"process ID of the "},{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" process that owns the VM."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Other commands (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stop"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"list"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ip"},{"text":") read the PID file to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"determine whether a VM is running and to signal the process.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"PID File Lifecycle","anchor":"PID-File-Lifecycle","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"spook start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" writes the PID file before booting the VM.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook stop"},{"text":" reads the PID file and sends SIGTERM.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook start"},{"text":" installs a SIGTERM handler that gracefully","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stops the VM, removes the PID file, and exits.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the process crashes, the PID file becomes stale.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" detects stale PID files by checking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"whether the recorded process is still running.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"text":"Thread Safety","anchor":"Thread-Safety","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"All methods are static and operate on the file system. They","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are safe to call from any thread. The PID file is a plain","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"text file containing a single integer, so reads and writes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"are effectively atomic at the file-system level.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/pidfile"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit7PIDFileO","title":"PIDFile","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"PIDFile","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"enum","roleHeading":"Enumeration","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Manages PID files for tracking running virtual machines."}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/fileName"],"anchor":"Type-Properties","title":"Type Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isProcessAlive(_:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/PIDFile\/isRunning(bundleURL:)","doc